For the second day in a row astronauts boarded space shuttle Endeavour on Friday for liftoff on NASA s first space station construction flight NASA has only five minutes or less each day to launch Endeavour in order to meet up with the first space station part which was put in orbit two weeks ago by the Russians The astronauts will use the shuttle robot arm to capture the Russian space station piece and attach it to Unity Endeavour and its astronauts closed in Sunday to capture the first piece of the international space station the Russian-made Zarya control module that had to be connected to the Unity chamber aboard the shuttle The job fell to Nancy Currie